01:06:33.148 --> 01:06:35.776
EPIC is very unique.

01:06:35.901 --> 01:06:39.738
It's a facility that has over 15
different agencies--state and local--

01:06:39.821 --> 01:06:42.240
that participate
in gathering intelligence...

01:06:42.324 --> 01:06:44.659
and making sure
that information gets out...

01:06:44.743 --> 01:06:48.705
to people in the field that need it
to stop drug trafficking.

01:06:48.830 --> 01:06:53.668
From here, we have the ability
to track vessels, airplanes, boats,

01:06:53.752 --> 01:06:55.837
anything that carries drugs.

01:06:55.962 --> 01:06:59.341
When the information comes in,
we're able to check
with different databases...

01:06:59.424 --> 01:07:01.344
to see if it's
in the system or not.

01:07:01.427 --> 01:07:04.138
And would most of that energy
be focused on the two cartels?

01:07:04.263 --> 01:07:08.684
The Juarez, the Obregon brothers--
Are those the two that would be
most important?

01:07:08.768 --> 01:07:11.354
Those are the two
clearest threats right now.

01:07:11.479 --> 01:07:14.107
They are the dominant force
in trafficking,

01:07:14.190 --> 01:07:16.275
both on the Mexican side
and in the U.S.

01:07:16.359 --> 01:07:19.487
How are the cartels achieving...

01:07:19.570 --> 01:07:22.740
the level of intelligence and
sophistication that they're showing?

01:07:22.865 --> 01:07:25.827
- Craig, why don't you answer that?
