Your Honor, ladies
and gentlemen of the jury,

02:08:12.668 --> 02:08:16.589
because of the sudden death
of Eduardo Ruiz,

02:08:16.672 --> 02:08:20.968
the people have determined
that we cannot continue our case
against Carl Ayala.

02:08:23.429 --> 02:08:26.432
Oh! Oh!

02:08:28.935 --> 02:08:31.229
Thank you so much.
Thank you, thank you.

02:10:16.628 --> 02:10:19.130
- Yeah?

02:10:19.214 --> 02:10:21.216
Hi.

02:10:22.300 --> 02:10:25.720
I got a copy of your speech.

02:10:25.804 --> 02:10:28.515
It's fantastic.

02:10:28.640 --> 02:10:31.184
So, Robert, my genuine thanks.

02:10:31.309 --> 02:10:33.436
You're my choice.
You're gonna be great.

02:10:33.561 --> 02:10:36.356
The president's sorry he hasn't been
able to spend more time with you.

02:10:36.481 --> 02:10:40.026
After the press conference,
he wants to really sit down.

02:10:40.151 --> 02:10:44.364
Oh, and I got to the Post too.

02:10:44.489 --> 02:10:47.200
Don't worry about that thing
with your daughter. It's not news.

02:10:47.325 --> 02:10:51.539
They're willing to treat it
as a family matter, personal matter.

02:10:51.664 --> 02:10:55.584
Anyway, if it came out,
we could turn it into a qualification.

02:10:55.668 --> 02:10:57.711
"I've been in the trenches
of the drug war.

02:10:57.837 --> 02:11:00.756
I've seen the face of the enemy.
Etcetera, etcetera. "

02:11:00.840 --> 02:11:05.678
A sterling reputation
and close friend of the president,

02:11:05.761 --> 02:11:09.390
recently confirmed into the Office
of National Drug Control Policy,

02:11:09.515 --> 02:11:14.228
our new drug czar,
Robert Hudson Wakefield.

02:11:24.697 --> 02:11:28.242
The war on drugs is a war
that we have to win,

02:11:28.367 --> 02:11:31.412
and a war that we can win.

02:11:31.495 --> 02:11:37.251
We have to win this war to save
our country's most precious resource--

02:11:37.376 --> 02:11:40.087
our children.

02:11:40.171 --> 02:11:44.634
Sixty-eight million children
have been targeted...

02:11:44.718 --> 02:11:47.762
by those who perpetrate this war...

02:11:49.222 --> 02:11:54.186
and protecting these children
must be priority number one.

02:11:57.898 --> 02:12:03.445
There has been progress,
and there has been failure.

02:12:03.570 --> 02:12:06.907
But where we have fallen short,

02:12:06.990 --> 02:12:10.452
I see not a problem,

02:12:10.577 --> 02:12:14.331
I see an opportunity.

02:12:17.751 --> 02:12:20.796
An opportunity...

02:12:20.921 --> 02:12:26.593
to correct the mistakes...
ofthe past...

02:12:26.676 --> 02:12:31.139
while laying a foundation
for the future.

02:12:36.771 --> 02:12:39.190
This takes...

02:12:39.273 --> 02:12:42.985
not only new ideas...

02:12:43.110 --> 02:12:46.030
but perseverance.

02:12:46.113 --> 02:12:51.911
This takes not only...
resources, but courage.

02:12:52.036 --> 02:12:53.996
This takes...

02:12:54.122 --> 02:12:57.333
not only... government,

02:12:57.458 --> 02:13:00.002
but families.

02:13:01.963 --> 02:13:04.006
I've laid out a--

02:13:07.426 --> 02:13:11.389
I've laid out
a ten-point plan that--

02:13:26.488 --> 02:13:28.407
I can't do this.

02:13:31.827 --> 02:13:35.873
If there is a war on drugs,

02:13:35.998 --> 02:13:40.043
then many of our family members
are the enemy.

02:13:43.505 --> 02:13:48.719
And I don't know how you wage war
on your own family.

02:14:31.888 --> 02:14:34.599
National Airport, please.

02:15:19.854 --> 02:15:23.983
Hey, Arnie, it's Saturday.
You're working too hard, my friend.

02:15:24.066 --> 02:15:27.319
Carl, I'm running late.
I'm coming right over.

02:15:27.403 --> 02:15:32.366
No, no, no, don't bother, Arnie.
Let me ask you something.

02:15:32.449 --> 02:15:35.369
When were you gonna tell me
about the $3 million...

02:15:35.453 --> 02:15:39.915
we got in from San Francisco
two days after I was arrested?

02:15:40.040 --> 02:15:43.961
Um... I was waiting
for the right time.

02:15:44.086 --> 02:15:47.339
Oh. You didn't think you could trust
my wife with that information?

02:15:47.465 --> 02:15:49.508
I didn't want to risk it.

02:15:49.633 --> 02:15:52.178
That could have been frozen
along with everything else.

02:15:52.261 --> 02:15:54.513
You had it all figured out,
didn'tyou?

02:15:54.638 --> 02:15:56.557
You were gonna move into my house,

02:15:56.640 --> 02:16:00.186
raise my kids, sleep in my bed...

02:16:00.311 --> 02:16:02.521
with my wife.

02:16:02.646 --> 02:16:04.900
Sounds like a nice plan.

02:16:05.025 --> 02:16:06.985
Oh, is it insane?

02:16:07.068 --> 02:16:09.696
Just think about it, okay?
If I was gonna rip you off,

02:16:09.821 --> 02:16:12.032
why wouldn't I just leave town
after Ruiz was killed?

02:16:12.157 --> 02:16:15.327
Why would I sit next to you
in court and listen to a dismissal?

02:16:15.410 --> 02:16:19.706
Let me ask you something.
You think there's a difference
between a reason and an excuse?

02:16:19.831 --> 02:16:22.375
'Cause I don't.

02:16:22.501 --> 02:16:25.796
- Good-bye, Arnie.
- Carl--

02:16:25.921 --> 02:16:27.881
Carl?

02:16:35.680 --> 02:16:37.891
Come on, sweetheart.

02:16:38.016 --> 02:16:41.061
Come outside.
Everyone's waiting for you.

02:16:41.186 --> 02:16:43.605
- Who was that?
- Arnie. He's, uh--

02:16:43.688 --> 02:16:45.898
- He can't make it to the barbecue.
- Oh.

02:16:46.023 --> 02:16:48.567
- Come on.
- Hi, Helena.

02:16:50.236 --> 02:16:52.155
- Hello.
- It's a great party.

02:16:52.280 --> 02:16:54.574
- Who is he, a friend of yours?
- Oh, I'm a nobody.

02:16:54.699 --> 02:16:57.245
I'm the nobody who arrested you.

02:16:57.370 --> 02:16:59.789
- You're--
- How you doing?

02:16:59.871 --> 02:17:02.290
- What are you doing in my house?
- Oh, just looking around.

02:17:02.375 --> 02:17:05.795
You got nice shit. Drug money
buys a lot of nice shit, Carl.

02:17:05.878 --> 02:17:08.214
Listen, you don't want to talk
that way in my house.

02:17:08.297 --> 02:17:10.424
You're fucking a murderer, Carl.

02:17:10.549 --> 02:17:12.968
- Fuck you and fuck your wife.
- Hey, you can't be in here.

02:17:13.052 --> 02:17:16.472
- Get him out.
- You put me out, Carl.

02:17:16.556 --> 02:17:18.558
- I'm a cop.
- I don't care.

02:17:18.641 --> 02:17:21.936
- Get out.
- Hey! Hey, hey!

02:17:28.692 --> 02:17:32.612
- Is that what you wanted?
- A nice little bedtime story, Helena.

02:17:32.697 --> 02:17:34.781
Tell him how you murdered
my partner!

02:17:34.906 --> 02:17:37.450
- You got the wrong--
- His name was Ray Castro, Helena!

02:17:37.576 --> 02:17:40.788
Ray Castro!
You remember that!

02:17:40.871 --> 02:17:43.124
- What's his problem?
- The carpet, sweetheart.

02:17:43.249 --> 02:17:45.168
- No, no, no, I got it.
- I got it.

02:17:48.254 --> 02:17:50.299
- Where did he come from?
- Outside, honey.

02:17:57.097 --> 02:17:59.016
What do you want to do, man?

02:18:28.629 --> 02:18:32.549
On the good days, I feel like I get it.

02:18:32.633 --> 02:18:36.553
Like it all makes sense.

02:18:36.637 --> 02:18:38.972
I can stay in the moment.

02:18:39.056 --> 02:18:43.852
I don't have to control
everything in the future...

02:18:43.977 --> 02:18:49.691
and I believe everything
is gonna work out fine.

02:18:52.986 --> 02:18:54.906
O-On the bad days,

02:18:56.657 --> 02:19:00.870
I just want to grab the phone
and start dialing numbers.

02:19:00.995 --> 02:19:04.707
I want to pull my hair...

02:19:04.790 --> 02:19:09.045
and run through
the streets screaming.

02:19:13.508 --> 02:19:18.555
But thanks to the people
I've met in these rooms,

02:19:18.680 --> 02:19:22.892
like Margaret and Jim...

02:19:23.017 --> 02:19:25.937
and Sarah,

02:19:26.020 --> 02:19:28.565
um...

02:19:28.690 --> 02:19:31.109
I'm pretty sure
I'm gonna make it...

02:19:31.191 --> 02:19:33.236
through today.

02:19:44.707 --> 02:19:47.251
Would you like to share?

02:19:48.544 --> 02:19:52.089
Uh... my name is Robert.

02:19:52.214 --> 02:19:55.134
My wife Barbara and I...

02:19:55.217 --> 02:19:59.096
are here to support
our daughter, Caroline,

02:19:59.180 --> 02:20:02.141
and we're hear to listen.

